blicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/picon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/02 6:30:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> I used root/nuke well into my 40's. I would pull with Flux staff, and high-tail it to my safe-spot for the area, then root the mob as soon as it was in range. Then I would back off to maximum DD range and start nuking. When root broke, I would generally stun (if it was a stunnable mob), re-root, and back to max DD distance again. Quite a lot more than you might expect form all the nasty things people have to say about root, it held through an entire fight, though the average was 2 roots per fight. The skin line of spells helped immensely. <p><table width = 30%><tr><td align=center style=filter:glow(color=#cc0000 strength=1)><font size=2 color=#ffff00 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</font></td></tr><tr><td align=center><font size = -1><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=23437>~ <i>profile</i> ~</a></font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uravensloche.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravensloche</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/02 6:53:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.crosswinds.net/~jester43615/wizard2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> this is similar to what i tried, but with one problem. I did not have sow, or any other type of haste spell. Therefore i could not run to max distance till after the mob was rooted.<br>
<br>
What i tried to do: Pull static gnoll spawn from spire with flux staff... immediately cast root. Root holds as mob is far enough away from spires to be out of aggro range of wandering mobs. Run to max distance, nuke, re-root as necessary.<br>
<br>
What usually happened: Pull with flux staff, cast root. root is resisted mob reaches me, beats on leatherskin. re-root, get interrupted. reroot again, it holds. start running to max dd distance, root breaks, mob follows. stop to re-root, mob beats down rest of leatherskin and starts to do damage. get stunned while casting root. become unstunned, panic, try casting DD spells while in melee. Fail miserably. Wait while loading.<br>
<br>
heh. Truth be told, it WAS the level of the mob that was my problem. I grouped last night in paw, asked group to let me experiment with the white gnolls (lower lvl then the tech mas ones). root held EVERY time. <br>
<br>
Regardless, I got 29 last night, and bought BoF. Now i am going to go practice with it on REALLY low mobs so that I know what i'm doing weith it, then SLOWLY move up the lvl chain of mobs till i see it being resisted a bit. And i'm not trying anything risky till i get a death buffer. hehe. <p>Yours in Blood,
<p>
<img src="http://www.v-d-p.net/sigs/ravensig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukalrieaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KalrieAF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/02 10:02:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> um, im uncertain as to why you would pull a mob with your Tstaff when you root / nuking.  Your first cast on a mob should be your bigest, baddest, slowest casting nuke spell you have.  Why you ask? Because its a free shot.  The mob has not agroed on you yet and is just standing there begging to be fried.  My point is, START the fight with the mob wounded.  If later in the fight it gets close, that one free nuke could make the difference between the mob running or you running =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukekenewah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kekenewah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/02 12:48:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> I root nuked from 16 to 29, and only died once.  I usually tried to hunt near zone lines if possible in outdoor zones.  From 16-18 did NK.  From 18-23 did base of Kurns tower.  From 23-29 did LOIO.  I always pulled from maximum distance with nuke that allowed me to cast from farthest distance.  Then root, nuke, repeat till dead. Only rarely did I have SOW.  It was very dangerous and took much longer than it just took my monk twink to go thru same levels, but it can be done with correct target choice.  If I noticed something resisted roots I would find another type of mob.  I tried to avoid fast moving mobs. BoF at 29 was a godsend. <p>Kekenewah Silverbear <BR>
Level 52 High Elf Wizard (01/22/02)<BR>
Drinal server <BR>
Order of the Silver Circle guild</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyahtzooba.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yahtzooba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/02 2:10:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> Approaching 44th and still root/nuke when soloing. BoF is truely a wonder! All that running around trying ta kite things wears my lil' butt out real quick, so I tend to work in a small triangle walking the target from point to point. If the target gets rooted, it is dead. If it breaks root, take the hit then root again. Many times I have charged the target to replace a broken root (if I wasnt far enough away for DD). Take the hit, then scorch its maggot-ridden hide.<br>
<br>
When I was huntin the gnolls it seemed that quite often I would get an exceptionally strong one compared to the previous dozen I had roasted. It could be that you encountered a couple &quot;boosted&quot; critters! Also, it might be my imagination, but I swear all targets get tougher when you are close to Ding!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://208.57.3.217/yaht/Boom41.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucumdar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cumdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/30/02 6:04:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Root&amp;Nuke</span><hr size=1> Next level you get BOF and everything changes.  I can usually kite with out SOW or Jboots.  SOW/boots is a must to multi-kite.<br>
<br>
Root and nuke works ok, but root sucks and none of the upgrades until elnerick's is worth it's salt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utoxxthewizard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toxx The Wizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/30/02 7:55:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root&amp;Nuke</span><hr size=1> Some mobs don't require snaring or sow/jboots.<br>
<br>
If you strafe, you can actually out run a lot of mobs. (undead for example)<br>
<br>
Hold right mouse button, and press forward + right/left at the same time.<br>
<br>
This only works on some critters, so beware. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=92172 "><IMG SRC="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg2/fierios/Toxx.txt" HEIGHT=168 WIDTH=375></a></center><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaeanorendarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/picon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/31/02 5:40:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root&amp;Nuke</span><hr size=1> The reason I pulled with flux staff was because in those days I liked to hunt busy areas. You can single pull much more readily with a non-damage means of aggro. Also, I pulled on the run to help avoid adds, and you can't nuke while running. I also didn't like to pull with BoF, because I wanted to get them to my safe spot as quickly as possible. Probably, I could have just nuked and killed most of them in place, but it would have taken more time to set up, watch pathing, etc. This way, once I had a good spot (or spots) for the area, I could hunt as fast as I could med. And yes, it did require SoW, and I spent lots on potions before I got my jboots. <p><table width = 30%><tr><td align=center style=filter:glow(color=#cc0000 strength=1)><font size=2 color=#ffff00 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe